From: AORUS 5090 platform repo <aobersnel@apnex.com.au>
Date: 2026-05-03
Subject: [PATCH] rcdbAddRmGpuDump: short-circuit on PDB_PROP_GPU_IS_LOST

Lever J-2 patch from /root/aorus-5090-gpu. Targets
NVIDIA/open-gpu-kernel-modules at tag 595.71.05.

Background
----------
When osHandleGpuLost declares the GPU lost (sets PDB_PROP_GPU_IS_LOST),
the recovery path calls RmLogGpuCrash which eventually invokes
rcdbAddRmGpuDump. That function calls into nvdDumpAllEngines_IMPL,
which iterates through every engine callback (~14 on Blackwell GB202).
Each callback issues a GSP RPC to read engine state. With GPU lost,
every RPC fails synchronously with NV_ERR_GPU_IS_LOST. The cascade
ends with journal.c:2239's NV_ASSERT firing, after which the kernel
deadlocks (deadlock locus captured in
/root/ollama/archive/lite-2026-05-03-211751/).

Fix
---
Add an early-return at rcdbAddRmGpuDump's entry on PDB_PROP_GPU_IS_LOST,
mirroring the existing early-return for PDB_PROP_GPU_TEGRA_SOC_NVDISPLAY
just below it. A GPU known to be lost has nothing to dump -- attempting
to dump it just exercises the deadlock-prone RPC cascade.

Adds an NV_DBG_ERRORS-level marker so we can observe the patch firing
in dmesg whenever a real GPU loss bypasses our Lever I retry budget.

Scope
-----
This is one of three Lever J-2 patches addressing L3 graceful failure
when the GPU is genuinely lost. Companion patches:
- 0003-nvDumpAllEngines-break-on-gpu-lost.patch (defence-in-depth)
- 0004-cleanup-asserts-accept-gpu-lost.patch (rs_client.c, rs_server.c,
  journal.c:2239)

Lever I (0001) prevents PDB_PROP_GPU_IS_LOST from being set on
transient PCIe failures. Lever J-2 patches keep the kernel alive when
the property IS set (real disconnect, transient longer than Lever I's
retry budget).

Related
-------
- /root/aorus-5090-gpu/docs/source-review-notes.md (Pass 5 + Pass 6 +
  Pass 8)
- /root/aorus-5090-gpu/docs/freeze-investigation-plan.md (Lever J-2)
- Captured deadlock evidence:
  /root/ollama/archive/lite-2026-05-03-211751/

---
 src/nvidia/src/kernel/diagnostics/journal.c | 14 ++++++++++++++
 1 file changed, 14 insertions(+)

diff --git a/src/nvidia/src/kernel/diagnostics/journal.c b/src/nvidia/src/kernel/diagnostics/journal.c
--- a/src/nvidia/src/kernel/diagnostics/journal.c
+++ b/src/nvidia/src/kernel/diagnostics/journal.c
@@ -2914,6 +2914,20 @@ rcdbAddRmGpuDump
     NvU32               bufferUsed;
     NvU8               *pBuf               = NULL;

+    //
+    // AORUS Lever J-2 patch (2026-05-03):
+    // Short-circuit on PDB_PROP_GPU_IS_LOST. A GPU known to be lost has
+    // nothing to dump; attempting to iterate engine callbacks via
+    // nvdDumpAllEngines just exercises the GSP-RPC failure cascade that
+    // deadlocks the kernel at journal.c:2239 (captured: 14 iter fn 78
+    // failures followed by host hang). See docs/source-review-notes.md
+    // Pass 5/6 for the captured kernel sequence.
+    //
+    if (pGpu->getProperty(pGpu, PDB_PROP_GPU_IS_LOST))
+    {
+        NV_PRINTF(LEVEL_ERROR,
+                  "AORUS Lever J-2 (rcdbAddRmGpuDump): GPU lost, skipping crash dump (was deadlock locus)\n");
+        return NV_OK;
+    }
+
     if (pGpu->getProperty(pGpu, PDB_PROP_GPU_TEGRA_SOC_NVDISPLAY))
     {
         return NV_ERR_NOT_SUPPORTED;
--
2.0
